{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:15:01.029Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploying 100+ (or 800+) agent instances is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"mass-agency"},{"type":"text","text":" pattern from the Rakuten case study: instead of one monolithic agent, you run a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"large swarm of many small, purpose-built agents"},{"type":"text","text":" that are automatically spawned, coordinated, and shut down by an orchestrator, so the system can handle thousands of concurrent workflows without blowing up cost or latency. The “800+ agent pattern” is basically the same idea at even higher scale: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"hundreds of specialized agents"},{"type":"text","text":" working in parallel, each optimized for a narrow task, with strict autonomy budgets, rate-limit distribution, and stateless workers."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Rakuten pattern is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multi-agent swarm architecture"},{"type":"text","text":" where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Orchestrator agent"},{"type":"text","text":": Receives the user goal, decomposes it into subtasks, and spawns specialist agents.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specialist agents"},{"type":"text","text":": Hundreds of small agents, each with a narrow domain (e.g., scraper, code-gen, analyst, writer).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dynamic spawning"},{"type":"text","text":": Agents are created on-demand, not pre-warmed.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Autonomy budgets"},{"type":"text","text":": Each agent has a limit on how many steps/tools it can use before it must report back.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stateless workers"},{"type":"text","text":": All state is externalized (Redis, database) so any worker can pick up any task."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"At 800+ agents, the pattern scales further:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"More specialization"},{"type":"text","text":": Even narrower domains (e.g., “Japanese e-commerce scraper” vs. “global scraper”).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Hierarchical pooling"},{"type":"text","text":": Pools of agents per domain, with load balancing across pools.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rate limit distribution"},{"type":"text","text":": Global LLM/tool quotas are split across workers.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Serverless fallback"},{"type":"text","text":": AWS Lambda or Cloud Run handles overflow spikes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of it like a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"mega call center"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- One manager (orchestrator).\n- Hundreds of agents (specialists).\n- Each agent handles one type of call.\n- New agents are hired on-demand.\n- Old agents are fired when done."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A single agent can only handle "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"10–50 concurrent users"},{"type":"text","text":" before latency degrades. At 10,000 users, you need:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"100+ agents"},{"type":"text","text":" in a swarm.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stateless workers"},{"type":"text","text":" with external state.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task queues"},{"type":"text","text":" for long-running jobs.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auto-scaling"},{"type":"text","text":" based on queue depth.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rate limit distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" across workers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without this pattern:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Latency spikes"},{"type":"text","text":" as more users queue up.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cost explodes"},{"type":"text","text":" (one agent doing everything = more tokens).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Errors increase"},{"type":"text","text":" (workers hit resource limits)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Rakuten pattern solves this by:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Parallelizing work"},{"type":"text","text":" across many small agents.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reducing cost"},{"type":"text","text":" (each agent does less → fewer tokens).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Improving reliability"},{"type":"text","text":" (failures are isolated to one agent)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the swarm as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"factory with many machines"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- One manager (orchestrator) assigns tasks to machines.\n- Each machine (agent) is purpose-built for one task (e.g., scraping, coding).\n- Machines are "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"auto-scaled"},{"type":"text","text":" (more machines when busy, fewer when idle).\n- All data is in a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"central warehouse"},{"type":"text","text":" (Redis/database), not on the machines."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"mass-agency"},{"type":"text","text":" architecture: many small agents, not one big agent."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Orchestrator-driven decomposition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The orchestrator receives the user goal and decomposes it:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"goal = \"Analyze market trends for AI startup pricing\"\nsubtasks = [\n    {\"task\": \"scrape\", \"domain\": \"scraper_jp_ecommerce\"},\n    {\"task\": \"analyze\", \"domain\": \"analyst_finance\"},\n    {\"task\": \"write\", \"domain\": \"writer_tech\"}\n]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For each subtask, the orchestrator "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"spawns a specialist agent"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"for subtask in subtasks:\n    agent = spawn_agent(subtask[\"domain\"])  # dynamically creates agent\n    agent.invoke(subtask)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agents are created on-demand, not pre-warmed."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Specialist agent pools"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agents are grouped into "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"pools"},{"type":"text","text":" by domain:\n- Pool 1: Scrapers (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"scraper_jp_ecommerce"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"scraper_global"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- Pool 2: Analysts (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"analyst_finance"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"analyst_healthcare"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- Pool 3: Writers (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"writer_tech"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"writer_legal"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The load balancer routes tasks to the right pool, then to the right worker:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"def select_pool(task: dict):\n    if task[\"domain\"].startswith(\"scraper_\"):\n        return \"scraper_pool\"\n    elif task[\"domain\"].startswith(\"analyst_\"):\n        return \"analyst_pool\"\n    else:\n        return \"writer_pool\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This isolates domains and balances load."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Stateless workers with external state"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All state is externalized to Redis or a database:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# worker.py\nimport redis\nfrom celery import Celery\n\nr = redis.Redis()\ncelery = Celery(\"agent_worker\", broker=\"redis://localhost:6379/0\")\n\n@celery.task\ndef run_agent(task_id: str, user_id: str):\n    # Load state from Redis\n    context = r.get(f\"user:{user_id}:context\")\n    result = agent.invoke(context)\n    # Save state to Redis\n    r.set(f\"user:{user_id}:context\", result)\n    return result"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This ensures "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"any replica can pick up any task"},{"type":"text","text":". If state is in-memory, only the original worker can continue that task, limiting scaling."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. Task queue for long-running jobs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"task queue"},{"type":"text","text":" (Redis, Kafka, Celery) for long-running agent jobs:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# orchestrator.py\nfor subtask in subtasks:\n    run_agent.send(subtask[\"domain\"], subtask)  # enqueues to queue"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Workers pull tasks from the queue and execute. This decouples request handling from execution, allowing workers to scale independently."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. Autonomy budgets"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each agent has an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"autonomy budget"},{"type":"text","text":" (max steps/tools before it must report back):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"class Agent:\n    def __init__(self, budget: int):\n        self.budget = budget\n        self.steps = 0\n    \n    def invoke(self, task: dict):\n        while self.steps < self.budget:\n            result = self.step(task)\n            self.steps += 1\n            if result.done:\n                break\n        return result"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This prevents agents from running forever and blowing up cost."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. Rate limit distribution"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Global LLM/tool quotas are split across workers:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"GLOBAL_RPM = 10000\nN = 100  # number of workers\nPER_WORKER_RPM = GLOBAL_RPM / N  # 100 RPM per worker"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each worker enforces its own 100 RPM limit locally. As long as requests are distributed evenly, the swarm stays under 10,000 RPM."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"7. Serverless fallback for spikes"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sudden spikes"},{"type":"text","text":", use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AWS Lambda"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Google Cloud Run"},{"type":"text","text":" to handle overflow:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# orchestrator.py\nif queue_depth > 50:\n    # Federate to serverless\n    run_agent_lambda.send(subtask[\"domain\"], subtask)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Serverless handles overflow (even if it costs more per-token). This is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"cost trade-off"},{"type":"text","text":": serverless is more expensive but handles spikes without over-provisioning."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Architecture"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical 100+ agent swarm stack:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  User Requests                                            │\n│  ↓                                                        │\n│  Load Balancer (ALB, Kubernetes Service)                │\n│  ↓                                                        │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐   │\n│  │ Orchestrator │  │ Scraper Pool │  │ Analyst Pool │   │\n│  │ Pool         │  │ Worker 1..N  │  │ Worker 1..N  │   │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘   │\n│       ↓                 ↓                    ↓           │\n│  Task Queue (Redis, Kafka, Celery)                       │\n│       ↓                 ↓                    ↓           │\n│  LLM (Claude) + Tools (Scrapers, Databases)            │\n│       ↓                 ↓                    ↓           │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │  External State (Redis, Database)                │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│       ↓                                                        │\n│  Serverless Fallback (Lambda, Cloud Run)                    │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Kubernetes + KEDA (auto-scaling)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# keda-scaledobject.yaml\napiVersion: keda.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: ScaledObject\nmetadata:\n  name: scraper-scaler\nspec:\n  scaleTargetRef:\n    name: scraper-worker\n  triggers:\n    - type: redis\n      metadata:\n        address: redis://redis:6379\n        key: scraper_queue\n        threshold: \"50\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This scales scraper workers based on queue depth."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Celery + Redis (task queue)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# worker.py\nfrom celery import Celery\n\ncelery = Celery(\"agent_worker\", broker=\"redis://localhost:6379/0\")\n\n@celery.task\ndef run_agent(domain: str, task: dict):\n    agent = get_agent_by_domain(domain)\n    return agent.invoke(task)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Run workers:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"celery -A worker worker --concurrency=10"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scale workers by adding more containers/pods."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handle thousands of concurrent users"},{"type":"text","text":" without degrading latency."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduce cost"},{"type":"text","text":" (each agent does less → fewer tokens)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Improve reliability"},{"type":"text","text":" (failures are isolated to one agent)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Elastic scaling"},{"type":"text","text":": Workers come online in seconds, process tasks, shut down when demand drops."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Aligns with "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"modern cloud infrastructure"},{"type":"text","text":" (containers, Kubernetes, serverless).\n- Handles "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"bursty traffic patterns"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g. spikes at 9 AM).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Independent scaling"},{"type":"text","text":": Pools scale independently."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Adds architectural complexity"},{"type":"text","text":" (task queue, external state, auto-scaler, rate limiting).\n- Requires "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"stateless design"},{"type":"text","text":" (externalize all state).\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monitoring overhead"},{"type":"text","text":": Track queue depth, worker count, latency, rate limit usage."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start with 10–50 agents"},{"type":"text","text":" for 5–50 concurrent users, then scale to 100+ as needed."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Externalize all state"},{"type":"text","text":" to Redis or database."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Add a task queue"},{"type":"text","text":" for long-running jobs."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use domain-based routing"},{"type":"text","text":" to route tasks to the right pool."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Set up rate limit distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" across workers."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monitor latency and error rates"},{"type":"text","text":" to know when to scale."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"100+ agent pattern = "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"many small, purpose-built agents"},{"type":"text","text":" in a swarm, not one monolithic agent."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Orchestrator"},{"type":"text","text":" decomposes tasks and spawns specialists on-demand."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Stateless workers"},{"type":"text","text":" externalize state so any worker can pick up any task."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Task queue"},{"type":"text","text":" decouples request handling from execution."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rate limit distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" splits global quotas across workers."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Serverless fallback"},{"type":"text","text":" handles overflow spikes."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
